modules.description: Contains a single test value that verifies the correctness of hash encoding and decoding operations. Works with integer identifiers and string-based hash representations. Ensures that encoded hashes are unique, reversible, and maintain a minimum length requirement.

This module implements bi-directional encoding of integer sequences into opaque string hashes and vice versa. It supports configurable parameters such as salt, minimum output length, and custom character alphabets to control hash generation. It is suitable for use cases like short URL generation, obfuscation of numeric IDs in APIs, and producing compact, reversible identifiers for database records.
